comments: RAR and LAR show Grant (OKC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Siakam's (TOR) driving shot attempt.

Gasol (TOR) makes inadvertent contact to Grant's (OKC) head that does not affect his ability to secure the rebound.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
LAR shows Siakam (TOR) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Schroder (OKC) that does not affect his SQBR.
Green (TOR) is already in Grant's (OKC) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Grant (OKC) legally contests Leonard's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
George (OKC) releases his dribble prior to lifting his pivot foot off of the floor.
Green (TOR) legally contests George's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Leonard (TOR) is in the lane for three seconds without actively guarding an opponent when the shot is imminent.
RLB shows George (OKC) places an arm on Leonard's (TOR) side but does not deliver contact that affects his SQBR.
George (OKC) initiates some contact with Green (TOR) in transition but he does not dislodge him from his position.
[Observable in enhanced video] Westbrook (OKC) moves his pivot foot on the perimeter.
RLS shows Gasol (TOR) makes contact to Westbrook's (OKC) arm/wrist that affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Leonard (TOR) briefly grasps George's (OKC) arm off ball, but the contact is marginal.
LAR shows Leonard (TOR) makes contact to George's (OKC) left arm/wrist as George is starting his upward shooting motion.
RAR shows Siakam (TOR) spins away from Schroder (OKC) and makes marginal contact that does not dislodge him from his position.
George (OKC) makes contact with Siakam (TOR) while he is airborne, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
RAR shows Schroder (OKC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends VanVleet's (TOR) driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (OKC) makes incidental contact to Leonard's (TOR) arm after he attempts the tip-in and the contact does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Green (TOR) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Westbrook's (OKC) driving shot attempt.
Schroder (OKC) establishes himself in a legal guarding position and Siakam (TOR) drives through and dislodges him.
VanVleet (TOR) legally contests Westbrook's (OKC) jump shot attempt.

Gasol (TOR) is already in Schroder's (OKC) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact to his upper body.  Any ensuing contact to Gasol's leg after the contact occurs to his upper body is considered incidental.
Grant (OKC) legally contests Leonard's (TOR) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
LAR shows Green (TOR) cleanly dislodges the ball from Grant (OKC).
VanVleet (TOR) makes contact to Adams' (OKC) arm after Adams has secured the loose ball.
RAR shows Leonard (TOR) makes incidental contact with Westbrook (OKC) on the perimeter.
RAR shows Schroder (OKC) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
LAR shows VanVleet (TOR) cleanly dislodges the ball from Grant (OKC).  After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of Thunder possession is overturned to Raptors possession.
Schroder (OKC) and VanVleet (TOR) briefly engage and separate off ball.
RAR shows Westbrook (OKC) makes incidental contact with Leonard (TOR) that does not affect his SQBR.
LAR and RAR show Westbrook (OKC) moves into Leonard's (TOR) body and affects his SQBR.
Gasol (TOR) is already in Westbrook's (OKC) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Westbrook (OKC) and VanVleet (TOR) make incidental foot to foot contact with one another on the perimeter.
Westbrook (OKC) legally contests VanVleet's (TOR) driving shot attempt.  Westbrook makes incidental contact with VanVleet after he lands following the shot attempt.
Schroder (OKC) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
RLS shows Green (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Schroder (OKC) on the perimeter.

Ferguson (OKC) makes contact to the body of Leonard (TOR) that affects his shot near the basket.  The basket is scored because Grant (OKC) makes contact with the ball after it touches the backboard with a chance to score.
RAR shows Adams (OKC) is already in Leonard's (TOR) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Gasol (TOR) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Westbrook's (OKC) drive.
Adams (OKC) is already in Leonard's (TOR) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Leonard (TOR) and Ferguson (OKC) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
LAR shows Leonard (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Westbrook's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Schroder (OKC) commits a take foul on VanVleet (TOR).
Leonard (TOR) cleanly deflects the ball away from Ferguson (OKC).
